This	O

,	O
Hyper	B-Protocol

Coffee	I-Protocol

Control	I-Protocol
Protocol	I-Protocol
,	O
and	O
is	O
not	O
expected	O
to	O
be	O
implemented	O
by	O
actual	O
HTTP	B-Protocol
servers	O
.	O
This	O
HTTP	B-Protocol
status	O
is	O
used	O
as	O
an	O

egg	O
in	O

,	O

as	O
com	B-Application
's	I-Application
"	O
I	O
'm	O
a	O
teapot	O
"	O
easter	O
egg	O
.	O
Sometimes	O
,	O
this	O
status	O
code	O
is	O
also	O
used	O
as	O
a	O
response	O
to	O
a	O
blocked	O
request	O
,	O
instead	O
of	O
the	O
more	O
appropriate	O
403	B-Protocol
Forbidden	I-Protocol
.	O
The	O
request	O
was	O
directed	O
at	O
a	O
server	B-Application
that	O
is	O
not	O
able	O
to	O
produce	O
a	O
response	O
(	O
for	O
example	O
because	O
of	O
connection	O
reuse	O
)	O
.	O
Indicates	O
that	O
the	O
server	B-Application
is	O
unwilling	O
to	O
risk	O
processing	O
a	O
request	O
that	O
might	O
be	O
replayed	O
.	O
The	O
client	O
should	O
switch	O
to	O
a	O
different	O
protocol	O
such	O
as	O
TLS/1.3	B-Protocol
,	O
given	O
in	O
the	O

header	I-Protocol
field	O
.	O
The	O
origin	O
server	B-Application
requires	O
the	O
request	O
to	O
be	O
conditional	O
.	O
Intended	O
to	O
prevent	O
the	O
'	O
lost	O
update	O
'	O
problem	O
,	O
where	O
a	O
client	O

state	O
,	O

and	O
PUTs	O

back	O
to	O

server	B-Application
,	O
when	O
meanwhile	O
a	O
third	O
party	O
has	O
modified	O
the	O
state	O
on	O
the	O
server	B-Application
,	O
leading	O
to	O
a	O
conflict	O
.	O
The	O
server	B-Application
is	O
unwilling	O
to	O
process	O
the	O
request	O
because	O
either	O
an	O
individual	O
header	O
field	O
,	O
or	O
all	O
the	O
header	O
fields	O
collectively	O
,	O
are	O
too	O
large	O
.	O
</s>
